WEBVTT

00:01.298 --> 00:03.332
You're the most amazing woman
I have ever met.

00:03.367 --> 00:07.436
Are you doing what I think
you're doing?

00:07.471 --> 00:09.372
Rachel Elizabeth Zane,

00:09.406 --> 00:10.740
will you marry me?

00:10.774 --> 00:12.975
- Yes.
- Yes?

00:13.010 --> 00:14.510
You want my permission
to take Mike

00:14.545 --> 00:16.212
and force him
to be your associate?

00:16.245 --> 00:17.647
Speak now or forever
hold your peace.

00:17.681 --> 00:18.748
I got us something.
It's the perfect way

00:18.782 --> 00:19.882
to consummate
our relationship.

00:19.917 --> 00:20.917
So just wait right here.
It's in the kitchen.

00:20.951 --> 00:22.718
- Sure.
- I can't let you do this.

00:22.753 --> 00:25.388
You're going back
where you belong.

00:26.456 --> 00:27.924
You never cared about me.

00:27.958 --> 00:29.225
All you care about is yourself.

00:29.259 --> 00:31.194
Louis, I'm not Norma.

00:31.228 --> 00:34.397
I told you I'd never let
anything happen to you.

00:34.431 --> 00:36.599
And I won't ever.

00:36.633 --> 00:38.100
I should go.

00:38.135 --> 00:40.136
Why?

00:40.170 --> 00:42.271
You know I love you, Donna.

00:42.306 --> 00:44.373
You ran away but not before
you told me you love me.

00:44.408 --> 00:46.709
I did that because I wanted
to make you feel better.

00:46.743 --> 00:48.311
I don't want your pity.

00:48.345 --> 00:50.346
You need to start thinking about
a new secretary.

00:50.380 --> 00:54.584
Harvey has no idea
how lucky he is to have you.

00:54.618 --> 00:56.385
[tense music]

00:56.420 --> 00:57.820
I'm leaving you, Harvey.

00:57.855 --> 00:58.921
You can't just quit.

00:58.956 --> 01:00.957
I'm not quitting.

01:00.991 --> 01:02.391
I'm going to work for Louis.

01:02.426 --> 01:06.362
♪ ♪

01:07.631 --> 01:09.465
So I told him I'll cave
on the billables,

01:09.499 --> 01:11.300
but if he wants someone
to kiss his ass all day,

01:11.335 --> 01:12.535
he'll have to settle for Louis.

01:12.569 --> 01:14.337
[laughs]
And what did he say?

01:14.371 --> 01:16.606
I don't know, but we got paid
and I haven't heard

01:16.640 --> 01:17.840
from him in a week.

01:17.875 --> 01:20.243
I have to say Harvey,
all things considered,

01:20.277 --> 01:22.545
you're taking this whole
Donna-Louis thing in stride.

01:22.579 --> 01:26.582
Well, I may have my issues,
but they only make me stronger.

01:26.617 --> 01:28.751
Good, because we're about to
walk into a room

01:28.785 --> 01:30.920
packed with people who think
they've got us by the balls.

01:30.954 --> 01:33.256
Well, I don't care what they
think, cause I'm gonna kill it.

01:33.290 --> 01:36.192
[dramatic music]

01:36.226 --> 01:37.760
What the hell's going on?

01:37.794 --> 01:39.896
What's going on is
I left you five messages

01:39.930 --> 01:41.831
and you never called me back.

01:41.865 --> 01:43.532
The meeting was over an hour ago
and you weren't here.

01:43.567 --> 01:45.034
Five messages?

01:45.068 --> 01:47.737
Please, you have to understand,
I lost my secretary.

01:47.771 --> 01:49.205
I don't give a shit.
I lost my company.

01:49.239 --> 01:50.239
No, you haven't.

01:50.274 --> 01:51.340
We can get them back.

01:51.375 --> 01:52.375
I can take care of it.

01:52.376 --> 01:53.709
Bullshit.

01:53.744 --> 01:56.712
You can't even
take care of yourself.

01:56.747 --> 01:58.381
Sorry, Harvey.
You're on your own.

01:58.415 --> 02:06.255
♪ ♪

02:07.257 --> 02:08.291
And then what happens?

02:08.324 --> 02:09.525
And then I get up.

02:09.559 --> 02:11.527
And how do you feel
when you get up?

02:11.561 --> 02:13.401
I told you I don't wanna talk
about how I feel.

02:13.430 --> 02:14.363
Then what are you doing here?

02:14.398 --> 02:15.898
You know what I'm doing here.

02:15.933 --> 02:18.868
I told you, your sleepless
nights aren't going to stop

02:18.902 --> 02:20.770
until you accept the fact
that your secretary

02:20.804 --> 02:21.971
isn't coming back.

02:22.005 --> 02:23.906
And I told you they'll stop
when she does.

02:23.941 --> 02:25.241
So just write me
another prescription

02:25.275 --> 02:27.043
and let me get some sleep
in the meantime.

02:27.077 --> 02:28.244
It doesn't work that way.

02:28.278 --> 02:29.278
Then how does it work?

02:29.313 --> 02:30.546
Why don't we start
with you taking me

02:30.580 --> 02:31.881
through the whole story again?

02:31.915 --> 02:33.549
What the hell good
is that gonna do?

02:33.583 --> 02:35.418
You want the truth?

02:35.452 --> 02:36.919
I think you might have
left some things out.

02:36.954 --> 02:38.554
Well, I didn't,
and I'm not about to

02:38.588 --> 02:40.056
go through this whole
damn thing again.

02:40.090 --> 02:41.891
Then go and find yourself
another doctor.

02:41.925 --> 02:43.459
Because I'm not writing
a prescription for anything

02:43.493 --> 02:45.094
without you talking to me.

02:45.128 --> 02:48.030
♪ ♪

02:48.065 --> 02:50.366
[Mike sighs]

02:50.400 --> 02:52.034
[Mike chuckles]

02:56.106 --> 02:57.606
[laughs softly]

02:57.641 --> 03:00.876
I...I can't stop
staring at it.

03:00.911 --> 03:02.845
Oh, I noticed.

03:02.879 --> 03:05.748
Yeah.
So will everyone else.

03:05.782 --> 03:07.550
Well, I mean, yeah,
that's the point.

03:07.584 --> 03:10.386
For everyone to realize
that you're my property.

03:10.420 --> 03:11.420
[laughs]
Okay.

03:11.421 --> 03:12.621
Are you saying you own me now?

03:12.656 --> 03:13.923
Oh, hell yeah,
and this here

03:13.957 --> 03:16.892
is just like a little collar
for your finger.

03:18.261 --> 03:19.762
[chuckles]

03:19.796 --> 03:22.064
- Mm.
- Mm.

03:22.099 --> 03:23.499
- Mike, seriously...
- Hmm?

03:23.533 --> 03:25.101
I know we told my parents
last night,

03:25.135 --> 03:28.204
but I was thinking that,
in terms of work,

03:28.238 --> 03:31.574
maybe we should keep it
to ourselves for a bit.

03:31.608 --> 03:33.743
I understand.

03:33.777 --> 03:35.711
- You do?
- Sure.

03:35.746 --> 03:40.082
You know, it's like
there's this bubble around us,

03:40.117 --> 03:42.685
and you just don't want it
to burst yet.

03:42.719 --> 03:44.854
And you're okay with that?

03:44.888 --> 03:47.656
Rachel, you just agreed to spend
the rest of your life with me.

03:47.691 --> 03:50.326
Right now I'm pretty okay
with everything.

03:52.462 --> 03:53.763
Mm.

03:53.797 --> 03:55.064
- Then it's settled.
- Mm.

03:55.098 --> 03:56.132
We'll tell Donna
and that's it.

03:56.166 --> 03:57.833
What?

03:57.868 --> 03:59.468
What about the bubble?
There's no Donna in the bubble.

03:59.503 --> 04:01.170
Oh, come on, there's room
for Donna in the bubble.

04:01.204 --> 04:03.706
You realize I get to sleep with
whoever's in the bubble, right?

04:03.740 --> 04:05.875
So long as you realize
that my dad's in the bubble.

04:05.909 --> 04:07.143
Donna it is.

04:07.177 --> 04:09.045
[laughs]

04:09.079 --> 04:11.080
Come here.
All right.

04:11.114 --> 04:12.448
Remember that thing online?

04:12.482 --> 04:14.183
- [laughs]
- We're doing it.

04:18.588 --> 04:19.688
Donna, what the hell
are you doing?

04:19.723 --> 04:21.257
What does it look like
I'm doing?

04:21.291 --> 04:22.425
I'm getting rid
of these résumés.

04:22.459 --> 04:25.294
No, no. Oh, my God, woman,
are you crazy?

04:25.328 --> 04:28.064
I have interviews with Norma's
replacements in ten minutes.

04:28.098 --> 04:29.932
Oh, that's gonna be hard
considering the fact

04:29.966 --> 04:31.567
that I canceled
all your interviews.

04:31.601 --> 04:33.536
Damn it, Donna, those were
the best candidates in the city.

04:33.570 --> 04:37.640
No, Louis, the best candidate
in the city

04:37.674 --> 04:40.176
is standing right
in front of you.

04:40.210 --> 04:41.544
But you told me no.

04:41.578 --> 04:44.146
And now I'm saying yes.

04:44.181 --> 04:47.483
This is the most amazing moment
in my entire life.

04:47.517 --> 04:49.251
Good.

04:49.286 --> 04:50.286
I'll get you a temp
for a couple of weeks

04:50.320 --> 04:52.621
and then we'll get started.

04:52.656 --> 04:53.656
Wait, I'm sorry, wait.

04:53.657 --> 04:55.157
You haven't told Harvey yet?

04:55.192 --> 04:58.227
I told him. I just--
I have to give him two weeks.

04:58.261 --> 05:01.430
Okay, you know what,
on second thought,

05:01.465 --> 05:03.199
as much as I appreciate
the gesture,

05:03.233 --> 05:04.600
I think you should just stay
with Harvey.

05:04.634 --> 05:06.068
What are you talking about?
This isn't a gesture.

05:06.103 --> 05:07.236
No, look, you just--

05:07.270 --> 05:10.873
Do you remember
Mike almost became my associate?

05:10.907 --> 05:12.475
(Louis) What am I talking about?
Of course you do.

05:12.509 --> 05:15.311
Well then, you'll also remember
that just as Mike had said yes,

05:15.345 --> 05:17.279
Harvey swoops in
and he takes him back from me

05:17.314 --> 05:18.314
at the last second.

05:18.315 --> 05:19.515
That isn't gonna happen.

05:19.549 --> 05:22.118
What you don't know
is that I left the room.

05:22.152 --> 05:24.553
I went to get Mike this cake
that said,

05:24.588 --> 05:26.589
"Welcome to Team Litt."

05:26.623 --> 05:29.024
Two minutes later, I come back
and there they are,

05:29.059 --> 05:32.661
high-fiving, laughing,
and then they leave.

05:32.696 --> 05:34.663
[somber music]

05:34.698 --> 05:35.831
I threw the cake out.

05:35.866 --> 05:39.935
♪ ♪

05:39.970 --> 05:43.906
I cannot have that happen again
with you.

05:43.940 --> 05:46.342
Louis, I told you
that isn't gonna happen.

05:46.376 --> 05:48.644
Did you not just hear me?

05:48.678 --> 05:50.579
It took Harvey two minutes
to steal Mike back from me.

05:50.614 --> 05:52.414
With you, he has two weeks.

05:52.449 --> 05:55.718
♪ ♪

05:55.752 --> 05:56.752
So no thank you.

05:56.753 --> 06:04.093
♪ ♪

06:04.127 --> 06:06.896
Donna, I need to get in touch
with Henderson before lunch,

06:06.930 --> 06:08.831
and I need to get
Braxton a bottle of wine.

06:08.865 --> 06:09.932
I took care of all that.

06:09.966 --> 06:13.035
Good.
Thanks.

06:13.069 --> 06:15.704
Is there anything else
you want to talk about?

06:15.739 --> 06:17.339
Not that I can think of.

06:17.374 --> 06:18.674
Did you really think
that if you just acted

06:18.708 --> 06:21.944
like I changed my mind
that I'd change my mind?

06:21.978 --> 06:23.479
Oh, come on, Donna, Louis?

06:23.513 --> 06:25.281
I mean, how long do you think
that's going to last?

06:25.315 --> 06:27.716
It's gonna last however long
I want it to last.

06:27.751 --> 06:31.220
- Donna--
- Harvey, this is happening.

06:31.254 --> 06:32.521
This is my formal notice.

06:32.556 --> 06:34.390
But I have no intention
of leaving you high and dry,

06:34.424 --> 06:36.792
so let's talk about finding you
someone in the next two weeks.

06:36.826 --> 06:38.260
- Finding me someone?
- Yes.

06:38.295 --> 06:41.063
I already have a list of the top
legal secretaries in the city.

06:41.097 --> 06:42.364
You mean you made a list
for Louis

06:42.399 --> 06:44.066
before you decided
to abandon me?

06:44.100 --> 06:46.602
I'm not abandoning you, Harvey.
I'm doing what's best for me.

06:46.636 --> 06:48.804
Well, as long as we're doing
what's best for ourselves,

06:48.838 --> 06:50.105
you know what's best for me?

06:50.140 --> 06:51.307
Ripping the Band-Aid off.

06:51.341 --> 06:52.408
- Harvey--
- So why don't you clean out

06:52.442 --> 06:54.510
your desk,
walk yourself over to Louis,

06:54.544 --> 06:56.378
and take that with you?

06:56.413 --> 06:59.248
[somber music]

06:59.282 --> 07:02.017
This isn't how two adults who
care about each other move on.

07:02.052 --> 07:03.852
As far as I'm concerned,
two adults

07:03.887 --> 07:08.257
who care about each other
don't move on at all.

07:08.291 --> 07:11.627
So, if you're gonna go,
just go.

07:11.661 --> 07:15.567
♪ ♪

07:15.568 --> 07:19.568
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Suits 5x01 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Denial</font>
